<br>
However, the Stonehand Robe is 3 less ac and about 1-2 less agi but I get 5 sta.  Which is better at 13?  The arms I think are a close call but I like Stonehand.<br>
<br>
Any comments are appreciated.<br>
<br>
Mae<br>
Newb<br>
E'ci <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unorpin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Norpin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Grand High Poobah</span><br>  Posts: 4035<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/12/02 2:23:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1877.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Stonehand v. Wu</span><hr size=1> Skip the Wu's chest.  Go straight for a Foreman Tunic, Lockjaw Hide Tunic, Spore Covered Tunic, or Crystal Covered Shroud. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bmonklybusiness43508.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=fopoodzo>Fopoodzo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master</span><br>  Posts: 690<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/13/02 12:06:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1877.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Stonehand v. Wu</span><hr size=1> Yep get a LJ tunic or something, but as to the others, I'd go with Wu's, more ac and agi is better than 5sta at L13 (unless maybe it pushes you over 100 or something, but even then). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umaewyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maewyn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/13/02 10:07:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1877.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Another couple questions...</span><hr size=1> Thanks.  As for LJ, that seems heavy.  I am too heavy and tend to be around 18-22 stones consistently.  I will keep researching.<br>
<br>
What is a typicaly inexpensive light 2hb to practice ($100 pp or less)?  I use a PSU for h2h but it is heavy and slow.<br>
<br>
My 1 hb's are good (given to me by brother when I started ~ Nobleman's and CoT).  I was given a Tranix helm, some nice neck piece, a spider cloak, earrings (pairs of orc and courgar) and a TBB.  He also gave me a hero bracer to use or sell.  Too heavy I think.  I use the orc fang over courgar claws due to the 30 hps total.<br>
<br>
Everything else is earned and stonehand, wu or cloth (face).<br>
<br>
Once I got to 17, I figured I would try this Paludal Cavern and maybe sell some of this stuff in bazaar (need to figure that out) and try for better monk pieces.  The hero bracer, TBB and Cougar claws should get me several hundred platinum (hopefully).  <br>
<br>
What is an inexpensive face and belt for me?<br>
<br>
Thanks again in advance.<br>
<br>
Maewyn<br>
E'ci<br>
<br>
