</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bmonklybusiness43508.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=fopoodzo>Fopoodzo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master</span><br>  Posts: 705<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/16/02 1:14:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1877.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Another couple questions...</span><hr size=1> Bear fanged gloves not a bad H2H weapon, tends to be cheap (I guess as non-magical but that's not usually a big deal). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uhotepthefriendlymonk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hotep the Friendly Monk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/18/02 1:39:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1877.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.swo.com/eq/domo1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Another couple questions...</span><hr size=1> The Adamantite Bo stick procs 3 waves of an AE rain, 75pts per wave. I used it to get my 2hb up before I hit 30 soloing the giant fort in Warsliks Woods and after 30 I kept using it on them - the proc was great fun with adds. It works great on giants because you can keep in melee range and out of the rain radius at the same time with only a little practice and effort. I've since used it duo-ing Seafuries in OOT with another monk friend. If all you're fighting is giants, it's great but for normal sized mobs you'll want a more conventional and better ratio 2hb. I've since given it to a friend to practice with and have replaced it with a Baton of Faith which I'm currently happy with.<br>
<br>
Hotep Apophis<br>
52 Monk<br>
Innoruuk <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uzinj.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zinj</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 2923<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/22/02 7:55:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1877.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Another couple questions...</span><hr size=1> Sleeves of the Stonehand &amp; Sleeves of the Silent Fist are slightly better than Wu's Fighting Sleeves.<br>
<br>
Lockjaw Hide Vest is slightly better than Foreman's Tunic, which is slightly better than Wu's Fighting Gi, which is slightly better than a Crystalline Silk Shirt, then Greyhopper Hide Tunic, then Dark Muslin Tunic, then Split Paw Hide Tunicand then Robe of the Silent Fist, and finally Robe of the Stonehand.<br>
<br>
Sandals of the Silent Fist is much better than Wu's Fighting Slippers, which is slightly better than Coteri Boots, then Kobold Hide Boots, and finally Sandals of the Stonehand.<br>
<br>
Gloves of the Stonehand and Gloves of the Silent Fist are just a little bit better than Wu's Fighting Gauntlets.<br>
<br>
Wu's Fighting Cap beats the heck out of the Cap of the Stonehand and Cap of the Silent Fist.<br>
<br>
Wu's Fighting Pantaloons are just slightly better than Trousers of the Silent Fist and Trousers of the Stonehand<br>
<br>
Wu's Fighting Wristbands are slightly better than Bracers of the Silent Fist, which are slightly better than the Bracers of the Stonehand.<br>
<br>
In all cases; if you play on a server that allows item looting; the Stonehands and Silent Fist armors are superior due to the fact that they are NO DROP.<br>
<br>
Zinj<br>
